						               													<description>Winnie the Pooh : Friends of the Forest Game&amp;#10;2-4 Players &amp;#10;Ages 5+&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Overview&amp;#10;Down in the Hundred Acre Wood, Pooh and his friends have fallen on hard times. The once crystal blue river has long since clogged up with rubbish and the trees which provide warmth and shelter for the animals are fast disappearing. &amp;#10;Woozles and Heffalumps are mischievous creatures, who wreak havoc in the wood chopping down trees, tossing rubbish in the river and generally making a nuisance of themselves.&amp;#10;Your task is to help Pooh clean the river and plant three trees.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Contents&amp;#10;1 Playing Area&amp;#10;27 Pooh Cards&amp;#10;28 Woozle Cards&amp;#10;4 Wooden Playing Pieces &amp;#10;1 Wooden Spinner (Top &amp;amp; Bottom) &amp;#10;12 Self Assembly Interlocking Trees&amp;#10;12 Jigsaw River Sections&amp;#10;2 Interlocking Woodland Sections&amp;#10;1 Dice&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Object of the Game&amp;#10;To be the first player to clean up the river and plant three trees in his/her area&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay&amp;#10;Players roll a die and move around the board planting trees and cleaning river sections.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player lands on a Spin the cloud space the weather cloud is spun and effects are applied to the players areas&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Sunny &amp;ndash; Take a tree&amp;#10;Stormy &amp;ndash; Lose a tree but clean a river section&amp;#10;Pollution &amp;ndash; Lose a tree and a clean river section&amp;#10;Gloomy &amp;ndash; Your area is unaffected&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Trees and Rivers can also be lost and gained through cards and other board spaces&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
